PRACTICAL 5: Accessing iSCSI Storage
Prerequisites

• Practical 1, 2, and 4 completed
• Standard switch configured
• iSCSI target available

Steps

Log in to ESXi Host Client and navigate to Storage Adapters.

Verify existing iSCSI software adapter configuration.

Create a new VMkernel Port Group for iSCSI traffic.

Assign IP address to the VMkernel adapter.

Enable iSCSI software adapter if not already enabled.

Configure Dynamic Discovery by adding iSCSI target IP address.

Perform rescan to detect available storage.

Verify successful connection between ESXi host and iSCSI storage.
